    quiz: [{ question: "A parent asks the nurse about the best time to apply moisturizer to their child with atopic dermatitis. What is the correct response?", options: ["Apply moisturizer to completely dry skin before bedtime only", "Apply a thick layer of moisturizer within 3 minutes after bathing", "Apply moisturizer 30 minutes after bathing to allow skin to air-dry", "Moisturizer is not needed if topical corticosteroids are being used"], correct: 1, rationale: "The soak-and-seal technique involves applying emollient within 3 minutes of bathing to trap moisture in the skin and restore the impaired epidermal barrier. This is the foundation of atopic dermatitis management." }]
