    quiz: [{ question: "A patient presents with intensely pruritic linear vesicular lesions on both forearms after gardening. What is the priority nursing action?", options: ["Apply topical antibiotics to the lesions immediately", "Identify and remove the offending agent and cleanse the skin", "Prepare the patient for an immediate skin biopsy", "Administer intravenous corticosteroids"], correct: 1, rationale: "The priority is identifying and removing the offending agent (likely poison ivy based on the linear vesicular pattern after gardening) and cleansing the skin to remove residual allergen. This prevents further exposure and limits the immune response. Linear vesicular streaks are characteristic of plant-derived allergic contact dermatitis." }]
