    quiz: [{ question: "A patient with pemphigus vulgaris has painful oral erosions and flaccid blisters on the trunk. Which nursing intervention is most important for this patient's comfort and nutrition?", options: ["Encourage the patient to eat spicy foods to stimulate appetite", "Provide gentle oral care and offer a soft, bland, high-protein diet", "Apply adhesive bandages directly to blisters for protection", "Encourage vigorous tooth brushing to maintain oral hygiene"], correct: 1, rationale: "Patients with pemphigus vulgaris often have painful oral erosions that make eating extremely difficult. Providing gentle oral care (soft-bristled brush, non-irritating mouthwash) and a soft, bland, high-protein diet promotes nutrition while minimizing pain. Spicy foods and vigorous brushing would worsen oral pain, and adhesive bandages could further damage fragile skin." }]
